items.title: Thomas Cook (India) reports net profit of Rs 66.4 cr for Q2FY26, revenues at Rs 2074 cr
items.description: Thomas Cook India has reported a net profit of Rs 66.4 crore for the September quarter. Revenue from operations saw a 3.5% rise. The company demonstrated resilience despite global challenges. Forex business and retail sales showed growth. New properties were added by Sterling Holidays. App bookings and Forex by WhatsApp transactions also increased. The company maintains a strong financial position.

items.title: Tata Steel’s Q2 consolidated profit surges fourfold to Rs 3,183 crore
items.description: Tata Steel reported a significant profit jump in the September quarter. India operations drove strong volume growth. The Netherlands unit saw a sharp rise in operating profit. The company also narrowed losses in its UK operations. Sales increased year-on-year. Earnings before interest, tax, depreciation, and amortisation rose substantially.

items.title: Ashok Leyland net profit up 7% at Rs 820 crore
items.description: Ashok Leyland reported a record consolidated net profit of ₹820 crore in the September quarter, a 7% increase year-on-year, driven by broad-based segment recovery and operational efficiencies. Consolidated revenue also rose 13% to ₹12,577 crore, with the company achieving its 12th consecutive quarter of double-digit Ebitda margin.

items.title: Q2 results today: Investors will see whether LG India justifies wave of buy calls it received after IPO
items.description: LG Electronics India, a successful 2025 listing, is set to announce its first quarterly results today. The company, which saw over 50% listing gains, will face investor scrutiny on whether its strong fundamentals and market leadership justify the post-IPO euphoria. Analysts remain optimistic about its growth trajectory and profitability.

items.title: Asian Paints reports strong Q2 earnings with double-digit growth in decorative paints
items.description: Asian Paints achieved strong sales growth in decorative paints, marking a significant turnaround. The company's profit also saw year-on-year improvement. This positive performance comes despite challenging market conditions. Demand is expected to be supported by upcoming festive seasons and agricultural output. Asian Paints continues to focus on cost efficiencies and brand investments.

items.title: LG Electronics India Q2 Results: Profit falls 27% YoY to Rs 389 crore; revenue stays flat
items.description: LG Electronics India Q2 Results: LG Electronics India reported a 27% year-on-year (YoY) fall in its net profit at Rs 389 crore in the second quarter. The same stood at Rs 536 crore in the year-ago quarter. Revenue from operations, meanwhile, rose by a marginal 1% YoY to Rs 6,174 crore.

items.title: Tata Motors (CV) Q2: First results post-listing show Rs 867 crore YoY loss on Tata Capital mark-down; revenue up 6%
items.description: Tata Motors CV Q2 Results: Tata Motors Ltd on Thursday reported a consolidated net loss at Rs 867 crore versus a net profit of Rs 498 crore in the year ago period. The company's revenue form operations in the quarter stood at Rs 18,585 crore, up 6% over Rs 17,535 crore in the corresponding quarter of the last financial year.

items.title: Voltas Q2 Results: Profit plunges 76% to Rs 31 crore
items.description: Air-conditioning manufacturer and engineering services provider Voltas Ltd on Thursday reported a 76.28 per cent decline in consolidated net profit to Rs 31.5 crore for the September quarter of FY26, as a subdued summer season and GST-related demand deferment weighed on its cooling business.

items.title: Jubilant Foodworks Q2 net profit up twofold to Rs 194.6cr, revenue up 19.7 pc to Rs 2,340 cr
items.description: Jubilant Foodworks Ltd (JFL), which operates fast-food chains - Domino's Pizza and Dunkin' Donuts - on Thursday reported an over twofold jump in its consolidated net profit of Rs 194.6 crore in the September quarter of FY26.

items.title: Tata Motors PV Q2 preview: Earnings may hit a road bump on JLR cyber glitch. Revenue likely to drop up to 7.2% YoY. 5 things to watch
items.description: Tata Motors Passenger Vehicles will announce its September quarter earnings on November 14 amid the aftermath of a cyberattack at Jaguar Land Rover. Analysts expect revenue and PAT to show mixed trends, with domestic PV margins resilient, while JLR performance and global demand remain key monitorables for investors.

items.title: Eicher Motors Q2 Results: Cons PAT jumps 24% YoY to Rs 1,369 crore; revenue zooms 45%
items.description: Eicher Motors Q2 Results:  The company’s revenue from operations in the quarter under review stood at Rs 6,172 crore, up 45% from Rs 4,263.07 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous financial year.

items.title: Apollo Tyres Q2 Results: Net profit slips 13% to Rs 258 crore
items.description: Apollo Tyres on Thursday reported a 13 per cent year-on-year decline in its consolidated profit after tax to Rs 258 crore in the September quarter, hit by Rs 176 crore provision for its Netherlands-based plant restructuring.

items.title: Hero MotoCorp Q2 Results: Standalone profit rises 16% YoY to Rs 1,393 crore, revenue also up 16%
items.description: Hero MotoCorp Q2 Results: India's largest two-wheeler maker Hero MotoCorp reported 16% year-on-year (YoY) growth in its standalone net profit at Rs 1,393 crore. Revenue from operations too increased 16% YoY to Rs 12,126 crore.

items.title: Page Industries Q2 Results: Profit marginally down to Rs 195 crore
items.description: Apparel manufacturer Page Industries Ltd on Thursday reported a marginal decline in its net profit at Rs 194.76 crore in the September quarter.

items.title: Singapore Airlines Sept Qtr Results: Profit slumps 82% to SGD 52 million on Air India losses, lower interest income
items.description: Singapore Airlines Group on Thursday reported an 82 per cent fall in net profit to 52 million Singapore dollars in the September quarter as Air India losses and lower interest income hurt the bottom line.
